---
title: Component Registry
description: AI-readable component metadata for LLMs and code generation tools.
---

## Overview

The component registry is a machine-readable JSON file that describes Kumo Svelte components, props, variants, examples, and semantic tokens. It is designed for AI agents, code generators, and other tooling.

## Accessing the Registry

Read the generated JSON files from the source tree:

```bash
jq '.components.Button.props' packages/kumo-svelte/src/registry/component-registry.json
jq '.components.Button.props' packages/kumo-svelte/src/ai/component-registry.json
```

## Registry Contents

The registry includes component props with types and defaults, variant options, real examples, semantic color tokens, and sub-components for compound patterns.

## Svelte Notes

Use the Svelte registry files in `packages/kumo-svelte/src/registry/` and `packages/kumo-svelte/src/ai/` for this package. Do not rely on the upstream React registry when generating Svelte code because component APIs differ.
